[[[description]]]
This is used to denote whether a type is reference counted. A [`zval`](https://phpinternals.net/docs/zval) can be checked if it is reference counted via the [`Z_REFCOUNTED`](http://phpinternals.net/docs/z_refcounted) macro.

The following types are refcounted:
 - [Strings](http://phpinternals.net/categories/zend_strings) (non-interned only)
 - [Objects](http://phpinternals.net/categories/zend_objects)
 - [Arrays](http://phpinternals.net/categories/zend_arrays) (mutable only)
 - Resources
 - [References](https://phpinternals.net/categories/zend_references)

See the [Garbage Collector](https://phpinternals.net/categories/garbage_collector) for more information on reference counting.

